## Objective

Add a dynamic placeholder that changes based on streaming state, and thread the `isStreaming` boolean properly through the component hierarchy.

## Files to Modify

- `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/ChatInput.tsx`
- `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/ChatInputContainer.tsx`

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Add `placeholder` prop to ChatInput

In `ChatInput.tsx`, add an optional `placeholder` prop to `ChatInputProps`:

```typescript
interface ChatInputProps {
  // ... existing props
  /** Custom placeholder text for the textarea. Defaults to "Message Claude...". */
  placeholder?: string;
}
```

Update the destructured props to include `placeholder` with a default:
```typescript
{
  // ... existing props
  placeholder = 'Message Claude...',
}
```

Update the textarea element (current line 247) from hardcoded `placeholder="Message Claude..."` to `placeholder={placeholder}`.

### 2. Compute dynamic placeholder in ChatInputContainer

In `ChatInputContainer.tsx`, compute the `isStreaming` boolean locally from the existing `status` prop:

```typescript
const isStreaming = status === 'streaming';
```

Compute the placeholder value based on state:
```typescript
const placeholder = isStreaming
  ? 'Compose next \u2014 will send when ready'
  : 'Message Claude...';
```

Pass it to the `ChatInput` component:
```typescript
<ChatInput
  ref={chatInputRef}
  value={input}
  onChange={autocomplete.handleInputChange}
  onSubmit={handleSubmit}
  isLoading={status === 'streaming' || isUploading}
  sessionBusy={sessionBusy}
  onStop={stop}
  onEscape={autocomplete.dismissPalettes}
  onClear={() => {
    setInput('');
    autocomplete.dismissPalettes();
