## Objective

Create the `useMessageQueue` hook that manages a FIFO message queue, provides CRUD operations for queue items, tracks editing state, auto-flushes queued messages when the agent transitions from streaming to idle, and cleans up on session/cwd changes.

## Files to Create

- `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/use-message-queue.ts`

## Full Implementation

```typescript
import { useState, useEffect, useRef, useCallback } from 'react';
import type { ChatStatus } from './chat-types';

/** A single item in the message queue. */
export interface QueueItem {
  id: string;
  content: string;
  createdAt: number;
}

interface UseMessageQueueOptions {
  status: ChatStatus;
  sessionBusy: boolean;
  sessionId: string | null;
  selectedCwd: string | null;
  onFlush: (content: string) => void;
}

interface UseMessageQueueReturn {
  queue: QueueItem[];
  editingIndex: number | null;
  addToQueue: (content: string) => void;
  updateQueueItem: (index: number, content: string) => void;
  removeFromQueue: (index: number) => void;
  startEditing: (index: number) => string;
  cancelEditing: () => void;
  saveEditing: (content: string) => void;
  clearQueue: () => void;
}
```

### State Management

- `queue` via `useState<QueueItem[]>([])` ‚Äî triggers renders for QueuePanel
- `editingIndex` via `useState<number | null>(null)` ‚Äî which queue item is loaded in textarea
- `onFlushRef` via `useRef` ‚Äî avoids stale closure in auto-flush effect
- `prevStatusRef` via `useRef<ChatStatus>('idle')` ‚Äî detects idle transition

### Auto-Flush Effect

The auto-flush fires when `status` transitions from `'streaming'` to `'idle'`. It takes the first non-editing item from the queue, prepends a timing annotation, removes it from the queue, adjusts `editingIndex` if needed, and calls `onFlushRef.current(annotatedContent)`.

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  if (prevStatusRef.current === 'streaming' && status === 'idle') {
    if (queue.length > 0 && !sessionBusy) {
      const firstNonEditing = editingIndex === 0
        ? queue.length > 1 ? 1 : null
        : 0;
      if (firstNonEditing !== null) {
        const item = queue[firstNonEditing];
        const annotated = `[Note: This message was composed while the agent was responding to the previous message]\n\n${item.content}`;
        setQueue(prev => prev.filter((_, i) => i !== firstNonEditing));
        if (editingIndex !== null && editingIndex > firstNonEditing) {
          setEditingIndex(prev => prev !== null ? prev - 1 : null);
        }
        onFlushRef.current(annotated);
      }
    }
  }
  prevStatusRef.current = status;
}, [status, sessionBusy, queue, editingIndex]);
```

### Cleanup Effect

Clear queue on session or cwd change:
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  setQueue([]);
  setEditingIndex(null);
}, [sessionId, selectedCwd]);
```

### Method Implementations

- `addToQueue(content)`: If `!content.trim()` return early. Otherwise append `{ id: crypto.randomUUID(), content, createdAt: Date.now() }` to queue.
- `updateQueueItem(index, content)`: Replace content at index using functional setState, preserve `id` and `createdAt`.
- `removeFromQueue(index)`: Filter out item at index. If `editingIndex === index`, set `editingIndex = null`. If `editingIndex > index`, decrement `editingIndex`.
- `startEditing(index)`: Set `editingIndex = index`, return `queue[index].content` so the caller can load it into the textarea.
- `cancelEditing()`: Set `editingIndex = null`.
- `saveEditing(content)`: Call `updateQueueItem(editingIndex!, content)`, then set `editingIndex = null`.
- `clearQueue()`: Set `queue = []`, `editingIndex = null`.

All methods should be wrapped in `useCallback` with appropriate dependencies.

## Testing Requirements

Create `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/__tests__/use-message-queue.test.ts`:

