- [ ] All CRUD methods work correctly
- [ ] Auto-flush fires only on streaming-to-idle transition
- [ ] Timing annotation is prepended to flushed content
- [ ] Auto-flush skips items being edited
- [ ] Queue clears on session/cwd change
- [ ] All 16 tests written and passing
- [ ] `QueueItem` type is exported

## Objective

Add a `submitContent` method to `useChatSession` that accepts content directly as a string parameter, bypassing the `input` state. This is needed for the auto-flush mechanism in `useMessageQueue`, which must submit queued messages without manipulating the textarea's `input` state.

## Files to Modify

- `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/use-chat-session.ts`
- `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/chat-types.ts` (if needed for type export)

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Add `submitContent` method inside `useChatSession`

The existing `handleSubmit` (line 340) reads from `input` state and guards with `if (!input.trim() || status === 'streaming') return`. The new `submitContent` method accepts content directly:

```typescript
const submitContent = useCallback(async (content: string) => {
  if (!content.trim() || status === 'streaming') return;

  // Create session on first message if no active session
  let targetSessionId = sessionId;
  if (!targetSessionId) {
    targetSessionId = crypto.randomUUID();
    const now = new Date().toISOString();
    insertOptimisticSession(queryClient, selectedCwdRef.current, {
      id: targetSessionId,
      title: `Session ${targetSessionId.slice(0, 8)}`,
      createdAt: now,
      updatedAt: now,
      permissionMode: 'default',
    });
    onSessionIdChangeRef.current?.(targetSessionId);
  }

  const userContent = content.trim();
  const userMessage: ChatMessage = {
    id: crypto.randomUUID(),
    role: 'user',
    content: userContent,
    parts: [{ type: 'text', text: userContent }],
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
  };

  setMessages((prev) => [...prev, userMessage]);
  // Do NOT clear input ‚Äî submitContent is for programmatic submission (queue flush),
  // the textarea may have a user's current draft.
  setStatus('streaming');
  statusRef.current = 'streaming';
  setError(null);
  currentPartsRef.current = [];
  const streamStart = Date.now();
  streamStartTimeRef.current = streamStart;
  estimatedTokensRef.current = 0;
  setStreamStartTime(streamStart);
  setEstimatedTokens(0);

  assistantIdRef.current = crypto.randomUUID();
  assistantCreatedRef.current = false;

  const abortController = new AbortController();
  abortRef.current = abortController;

  try {
    // Apply transform (e.g., file prefix) to content
    const finalContent = transformContentRef.current
      ? await transformContentRef.current(userContent)
      : userContent;

    if (finalContent !== userContent) {
      setMessages((prev) =>
        prev.map((m) => (m.id === userMessage.id ? { ...m, content: finalContent } : m))
      );
    }

    if (relayEnabled) {
      const correlationId = crypto.randomUUID();
      correlationIdRef.current = correlationId;
      streamReadyRef.current = false;
      await waitForStreamReady(streamReadyRef, 5000);
      await transport.sendMessageRelay(targetSessionId, finalContent, {
        clientId: clientIdRef.current,
        correlationId,
        cwd: selectedCwdRef.current ?? undefined,
      });
      resetStalenessTimer();
    } else {
      await transport.sendMessage(
        targetSessionId,
        finalContent,
        (event) => streamEventHandler(event.type, event.data, assistantIdRef.current),
        abortController.signal,
        selectedCwd ?? undefined
      );
      setStatus('idle');
    }
  } catch (err) {
    if ((err as Error).name !== 'AbortError') {
      if ((err as { code?: string }).code === 'SESSION_LOCKED') {
        setSessionBusy(true);
        // Don't restore input for programmatic submission
        if (sessionBusyTimerRef.current) clearTimeout(sessionBusyTimerRef.current);
        sessionBusyTimerRef.current = setTimeout(() => {
          setSessionBusy(false);
          sessionBusyTimerRef.current = null;
        }, TIMING.SESSION_BUSY_CLEAR_MS);
      } else {
        setError((err as Error).message);
      }
      setStatus('error');
    }
    if (textStreamingTimerRef.current) clearTimeout(textStreamingTimerRef.current);
    isTextStreamingRef.current = false;
    setIsTextStreaming(false);
  }
}, [status, sessionId, relayEnabled, streamEventHandler, queryClient, resetStalenessTimer]);
```

### 2. Return `submitContent` from the hook

Add `submitContent` to the return object:
```typescript
return {
  messages,
  input,
  setInput,
  handleSubmit,
  submitContent, // NEW
  status,
  error,
  sessionBusy,
  stop,
  isLoadingHistory,
  sessionStatus,
  streamStartTime,
  estimatedTokens,
  isTextStreaming,
  isWaitingForUser,
  waitingType,
  activeInteraction,
  markToolCallResponded,
};
```

### 3. Consider extracting shared submission logic

The `handleSubmit` and `submitContent` methods share significant logic. To keep the code DRY, extract the common submission logic into a private helper function within the hook:

```typescript
const executeSubmission = useCallback(async (content: string, clearInput: boolean) => {
  // ... shared logic ...
  if (clearInput) setInput('');
  // ... rest of submission
}, [/* deps */]);
```

Then `handleSubmit` calls `executeSubmission(input, true)` and `submitContent` calls `executeSubmission(content, false)`. This avoids duplicating 60+ lines.

## Testing Requirements

Update `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/__tests__/use-chat-session.test.tsx`:

Note: This file already exists and has mock patterns established. Add tests:

1. `submitContent sends message with provided content` ‚Äî call `submitContent('test message')`, verify the transport's `sendMessage` or `sendMessageRelay` was called with 'test message'.
2. `submitContent does not clear input state` ‚Äî set input to 'my draft', call `submitContent('queued msg')`, verify `input` state is still 'my draft'.
3. `submitContent guards against streaming status` ‚Äî set status to streaming, call `submitContent('msg')`, verify no transport call is made.
4. `submitContent guards against empty content` ‚Äî call `submitContent('')`, verify no transport call.

