## Objective

Transform the ChatInput send button from a two-state (send/stop) model to a four-state (send/stop/queue/update) model, and update the Enter key behavior to support queueing during streaming and saving edits.

## Files to Modify

- `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/ChatInput.tsx`

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Update ChatInputProps interface

Replace `isLoading: boolean` with more granular props:

```typescript
interface ChatInputProps {
  value: string;
  onChange: (value: string) => void;
  onSubmit: () => void;
  isStreaming: boolean;        // Agent is streaming (replaces isLoading)
  isUploading?: boolean;       // File upload in progress
  sessionBusy?: boolean;
  editingQueueItem?: boolean;  // Currently editing a queue item
  queueDepth?: number;         // Number of items in queue (for badge)
  onStop?: () => void;
  onQueue?: () => void;        // Queue the current input
  onSaveEdit?: () => void;     // Save the queue item being edited
  onCancelEdit?: () => void;   // Cancel editing queue item
  onEscape?: () => void;
  onClear?: () => void;
  isPaletteOpen?: boolean;
  onArrowUp?: () => void;
  onArrowDown?: () => void;
  onCommandSelect?: () => void;
  activeDescendantId?: string;
  onCursorChange?: (pos: number) => void;
  onAttach?: (files: File[]) => void;
  placeholder?: string;
  // Queue navigation props
  onQueueNavigateUp?: () => void;
  onQueueNavigateDown?: () => void;
  queueHasItems?: boolean;
}
```

Note: `isLoading` is replaced by `isStreaming`. The uploading state is a separate concern handled by `isUploading`.

### 2. Derive button state

Replace the current `Icon` and button logic with a state machine:

```typescript
type ButtonState = 'send' | 'stop' | 'queue' | 'update' | 'hidden';

const isLoading = isStreaming || (isUploading ?? false);
const buttonState: ButtonState = (() => {
  if (editingQueueItem && hasText) return 'update';
  if (isStreaming && hasText) return 'queue';
  if (isLoading) return 'stop';
  if (hasText) return 'send';
  return 'hidden';
})();

const showButton = buttonState !== 'hidden';
```

### 3. Update button rendering

Import additional icons:
```typescript
import { ArrowUp, CornerDownLeft, Square, X, Paperclip, Clock, Check } from 'lucide-react';
```

Button icon and style mapping:
```typescript
const SendIcon = isMobile ? ArrowUp : CornerDownLeft;

const buttonConfig = {
  send: { icon: SendIcon, className: 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90', label: 'Send message', onClick: onSubmit },
  stop: { icon: Square, className: 'bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground hover:bg-destructive/90', label: 'Stop generating', onClick: onStop },
  queue: { icon: Clock, className: 'bg-muted text-muted-foreground hover:bg-muted/80', label: 'Queue message', onClick: onQueue },
  update: { icon: Check, className: 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90', label: 'Save edit', onClick: onSaveEdit },
  hidden: { icon: SendIcon, className: '', label: '', onClick: undefined },
};

const config = buttonConfig[buttonState];
const ButtonIcon = config.icon;
```

Render the button with a `relative` container for the badge:
```typescript
<div className="relative">
  <motion.button
    animate={{ opacity: showButton ? 1 : 0, scale: showButton ? 1 : 0.8 }}
    transition={{ duration: 0.15 }}
    whileHover={showButton && !sessionBusy ? { scale: 1.1 } : undefined}
    whileTap={showButton && !sessionBusy ? { scale: 0.9 } : undefined}
    onClick={config.onClick}
    disabled={!showButton || sessionBusy}
    className={cn(
      'shrink-0 rounded-lg p-1.5 transition-colors max-md:p-2',
      config.className,
      (!showButton || sessionBusy) && 'pointer-events-none opacity-50'
    )}
    aria-label={config.label}
  >
